This paper deals with the problem of parameter tuning in Statistical Machine Translation (SMT), which is a subfield of Natural Language Processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves optimization algorithms and objective functions, which are common topics in machine learning, particularly in the sub-fields of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of sentence length as a criterion for selecting a subset of the tuning dataset, which is a topic related to text processing and analysis, and could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
